<subSubSection id="0780EDEBA319FFFDFF7EF8C62484FF2D" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4F25BE60A319FFFCFF7EF8C625D8F809" blockId="14.[151,1437,1900,2032]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="7DEE6272A319FFFCFF7EF8C62154F87C" bold="true" box="[151,273,1900,1925]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium sized spiders with various color and marking patterns. Chelicera with two promarginal teeth and one unident retromarginal tooth. First tibia with three pairs of ventral macrosetae; first metatarsus with two pairs. Male palpal bulb large and wide, with obvious proximal tegular lobe; embolus usually long and coiled; retrolateral tibial apophysis finger-like. Epigynal window present with a median septum. Spermatheca swollen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F25BE60A318FFFDFF7EFF3D2484FF2D" blockId="15.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Similar in body form to 
<taxonomicName id="889AC5E3A318FFFDFE59FF322276FF49" box="[432,563,152,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Coryphasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DEE6272A318FFFDFE59FF322276FF49" box="[432,563,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Coryphasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the one unident retromarginal tooth on chelicera (
<taxonomicName id="889AC5E3A318FFFDFAF0FF3225D9FF49" box="[1305,1436,152,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Coryphasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DEE6272A318FFFDFAF0FF3225D9FF49" box="[1305,1436,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Coryphasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has one bicuspid retromarginal tooth) and the absence of the second spermathecae in the vulva.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0780EDEBA318FFFDFF2EFF4A25C0FE9D" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F25BE60A318FFFDFF2EFF4A25C0FE9D" blockId="15.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="7DEE6272A318FFFDFF2EFF4A217EFF01" bold="true" box="[199,315,224,248]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</emphasis>
Three species have been reported from South 
<collectingCountry id="378DFEF0A318FFFDFC8BFF752387FF0E" box="[866,962,223,247]" name="United States of America" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2B0BC391A318FFFDFC3CFF75243FFF0E" author="Platnick" box="[981,1146,223,247]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Platnick, N. I. (2012) The world spider catalog, version 12.5. American Museum of Natural History, online at http: // research. amnh. org / iz / spiders / catalog." type="book" year="2012">
Platnick 
<number id="F952AC47A318FFFDFBD7FF75243FFF0E" box="[1086,1146,223,247]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), of which only the 
<typeStatus id="902100C2A318FFFDFA85FF4A25D9FF01" box="[1388,1436,224,248]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="889AC5E3A318FFFDFF10FEAE2250FEE5" authority="Simon" authorityName="Simon" box="[249,533,260,284]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Ilargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coccineus">
<emphasis id="7DEE6272A318FFFDFF10FEAE2184FEE5" box="[249,449,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ilargus coccineus</emphasis>
Simon
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="2B0BC391A318FFFDFDBFFEAE22B4FEE5" author="Simon" box="[598,753,260,284]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Simon, E. (1901 b) Etudes arachnologiques. 31 e Memoire. L. Descriptions d'especes nouvelles de la famille des Salticidae (suite). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 70, 66 - 76." type="journal article" year="1901" yearSuffix="b">
Simon 
<number id="F952AC47A318FFFDFD43FEAE22A7FEE5" box="[682,738,260,284]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1901.0">1901</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
) has been well documented (
<bibRefCitation id="2B0BC391A318FFFDFBAEFEAE24A2FEE5" author="Galiano" box="[1095,1255,260,284]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1963) Las especies americanas de aranas de la familia Salticidae descriptas por Eugene Simon: Redescripciones basadas en los ejemplares tipicos. Physis B. Aires (C), 23, 273 - 470." type="journal article" year="1963">
Galiano 
<number id="F952AC47A318FFFDFB45FEAE24A2FEE5" box="[1196,1255,260,284]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2B0BC391A318FFFDFB1FFEAE2091FEC6" author="Edwards" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Edwards, G. B., Rinaldi, I. M. P. &amp; Ruiz, G. R. S. (2005) A review of some South American species of jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae) described by Mello-Leitao from Brasil, with resolution of the genus Asaphobelis. Biota Neotropica, 5, 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="2005">
Edwards et al. 
<number id="F952AC47A318FFFDFF7EFE8D2091FEC6" box="[151,212,295,319]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="889AC5E3A318FFFDFE88FE8221F4FEB9" box="[353,433,296,320]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Ilargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DEE6272A318FFFDFE88FE8221F4FEB9" box="[353,433,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ilargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much more diverse than that. Here we describe six new species discovered during expeditions to 
<collectingCountry id="378DFEF0A318FFFDFED2FEE621DEFE9D" box="[315,411,332,356]" name="Ecuador" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. The placement of these species in 
<taxonomicName id="889AC5E3A318FFFDFCCCFEE62330FE9D" box="[805,885,332,356]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Ilargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DEE6272A318FFFDFCCCFEE62330FE9D" box="[805,885,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ilargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is partly based on unpublished molecular data.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
